The paper discusses cyber security risk assessment and optimal cyber security strategies, which are topics that fall under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also introduces a game-theoretic model with uncertain payoffs, which falls under the category of game theory (cs.GT). The paper proposes a software tool that empowers organizations to compute optimal cyber security strategies given their financial constraints, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions the difficulty of quantifying risk, which is a topic that falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper specifically focuses on cyber security investments, which falls under the category of cyber security (cs.CYBER).
